org.jikesrvm.compilers.opt.regalloc

Class CompoundInterval

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<BasicInterval>, Collection<BasicInterval>, NavigableSet<BasicInterval>, Set<BasicInterval>, SortedSet<BasicInterval>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SpillLocationInterval

    class CompoundInterval
extends IncreasingStartIntervalSet
    Implements a live interval with holes; i.e. an ordered set of basic live intervals. There is exactly one instance of this class for each Register.

    The order that this set imposes is inconsistent with equals.

    This class is designed for use by a single thread.

      • removeIntervalsAndCache

        CompoundInterval removeIntervalsAndCache(CompoundInterval other)
        Removes some basic intervals from this compound interval, and returns the intervals actually removed.

        PRECONDITION: All basic intervals in the other interval that have the same begin as an interval in this compound interval must have the same end. For example, for a compound interval [(1,2)(2,3)], the other interval would be allowed to contain (1,2) and/or (2,2) but not (1,3).

        A violation of the precondition that would have an effect will trigger an assertion failure in assertion-enabled builds.

        Parameters:
        other - interval to check for intervals that we want to remove from this
        Returns:
        the basic intervals that were removed
